What you need to know:  The 48-year-old Frenchman will be marking his first Kenya start since 2002 when he steered a Citroën Xsara to fifth place, two years before starting his World Rally Championship (WRC) dominance.Loeb announced his return to M-Sport Ford’s line-up to the sixth round slated from June 23 to 26 at the scenic Rift Valley.